<subSubSection id="C3750A9EFF9AFFADFF7CC7A4FE51C6DD" pageId="2" pageNumber="96" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD05915FF9AFFADFF7CC7A4FEE1C589" blockId="2.[151,752,151,213]" box="[151,274,187,213]" pageId="2" pageNumber="96">
(
<figureCitation id="13544590FF9AFFADFF74C7A4FEF9C589" box="[159,266,187,213]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 2" captionStart-1="FIGURE 3" captionStart-2="FIGURE 4" captionStartId-0="3.[151,250,1860,1884]" captionStartId-1="4.[151,250,1924,1948]" captionStartId-2="5.[151,250,1874,1898]" captionTargetBox-0="[284,1303,184,1825]" captionTargetBox-1="[200,1384,188,1887]" captionTargetBox-2="[242,1346,181,1842]" captionTargetId-0="figure-30@3.[283,1303,181,1836]" captionTargetId-1="figure-18@4.[192,1395,181,1900]" captionTargetId-2="figure-30@5.[241,1346,181,1849]" captionTargetPageId-0="3" captionTargetPageId-1="4" captionTargetPageId-2="5" captionText-0="FIGURE 2. Rhopalopsole magnispina sp. n., male. a. terminalia, dorsal view; b. terminalia, ventral view; c. terminalia, lateral view." captionText-1="FIGURE 3. Rhopalopsole magnispina sp. n., male. a. terminalia, dorsal view; b. terminalia, ventral view; c. central plate, transverse bars and epiproct, dorsal view; d. epiproct, anterolateral view; e. epiproct, caudal view; f. tergum 10, lateral view. cp=central plate, tb=transverse bars." captionText-2="FIGURE 4. Rhopalopsole magnispina sp. n., male. a. subanal lobe, dorsal view; b. subanal lobe, ventral view; c. subanal lobe, dorsoapical view; d. subanal lobe, ventral lobe, caudal view; e. cleared subanal lobe, ventral view; f. cleared subanal lobe, ventrolateral view." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6577756" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6577759" figureDoi-2="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6577761" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6577756/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6577759/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/6577761/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="96">Figs. 2–4</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD05915FF9AFFADFF7CC61CFD20C4D5" blockId="2.[151,1437,259,1258]" pageId="2" pageNumber="96">
<emphasis id="B91B8507FF9AFFADFF7CC61CFF28C441" bold="true" box="[151,219,259,285]" pageId="2" pageNumber="96">Male.</emphasis>
Forewing length 6.0– 
<quantity id="4C97F4F0FF9AFFADFE3FC61CFDDAC442" box="[468,553,259,286]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.3" pageId="2" pageNumber="96" unit="mm" value="6.3">6.3 mm</quantity>
(n=2). Head brown to blackish, slightly wider than pronotum; compound eyes black; antennae brownish to brown, scape darker. Pronotum brown, surface with light brown longitudinal median stripes, corners obtuse, posterior portion slightly widened; wings membrane subhyaline, veins brown; legs brownish to brown. Abdomen brown, terminalia dark brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD05915FF9AFFADFF2CC68CFD68C601" blockId="2.[151,1437,259,1258]" pageId="2" pageNumber="96">
Terminalia. Tergum 9 sclerotized, anterior margin with heavily sclerotized, posteromedial portion produced in darkly sclerotized protrusion which is trilobed with three similarly sized apical triangular sclerites, each covered by dense black scales (
<figureCitation id="13544590FF9AFFADFE77C6C4FE09C4A9" box="[412,506,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1860,1884]" captionTargetBox="[284,1303,184,1825]" captionTargetId="figure-30@3.[283,1303,181,1836]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Rhopalopsole magnispina sp. n., male. a. terminalia, dorsal view; b. terminalia, ventral view; c. terminalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6577756" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6577756/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="96">Figs. 2a</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13544590FF9AFFADFDECC6C4FDD7C4A9" box="[519,548,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1924,1948]" captionTargetBox="[200,1384,188,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-18@4.[192,1395,181,1900]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Rhopalopsole magnispina sp. n., male. a. terminalia, dorsal view; b. terminalia, ventral view; c. central plate, transverse bars and epiproct, dorsal view; d. epiproct, anterolateral view; e. epiproct, caudal view; f. tergum 10, lateral view. cp=central plate, tb=transverse bars." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6577759" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6577759/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="96">3a</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate of sternum 9 slightly wider than long and rounded apically, basally with an oval hirsute vesicle (
<figureCitation id="13544590FF9AFFADFDDBC6E0FD7CC745" box="[560,655,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1860,1884]" captionTargetBox="[284,1303,184,1825]" captionTargetId="figure-30@3.[283,1303,181,1836]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Rhopalopsole magnispina sp. n., male. a. terminalia, dorsal view; b. terminalia, ventral view; c. terminalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6577756" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6577756/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="96">Figs. 2b</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13544590FF9AFFADFD71C6E0FD4AC746" box="[666,697,511,538]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1924,1948]" captionTargetBox="[200,1384,188,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-18@4.[192,1395,181,1900]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Rhopalopsole magnispina sp. n., male. a. terminalia, dorsal view; b. terminalia, ventral view; c. central plate, transverse bars and epiproct, dorsal view; d. epiproct, anterolateral view; e. epiproct, caudal view; f. tergum 10, lateral view. cp=central plate, tb=transverse bars." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6577759" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6577759/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="96">3b</figureCitation>
). Tergum 10 central plate with three separated sclerites, the mesal sclerite depressed and less sclerotized, posterior portion covered with a few hairs; transverse bars triangular, with a regular row of dense long hairs near outer margin (
<figureCitation id="13544590FF9AFFADFD07C558FCBAC73D" box="[748,841,583,609]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1860,1884]" captionTargetBox="[284,1303,184,1825]" captionTargetId="figure-30@3.[283,1303,181,1836]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Rhopalopsole magnispina sp. n., male. a. terminalia, dorsal view; b. terminalia, ventral view; c. terminalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6577756" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6577756/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="96">Figs. 2a</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13544590FF9AFFADFCBDC558FC68C73D" box="[854,923,583,609]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1924,1948]" captionTargetBox="[200,1384,188,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-18@4.[192,1395,181,1900]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Rhopalopsole magnispina sp. n., male. a. terminalia, dorsal view; b. terminalia, ventral view; c. central plate, transverse bars and epiproct, dorsal view; d. epiproct, anterolateral view; e. epiproct, caudal view; f. tergum 10, lateral view. cp=central plate, tb=transverse bars." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6577759" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6577759/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="96">3a, 3c</figureCitation>
). Lateral projections of tergum 10 a long and sclerotized spine-like plate which terminates in an acute point in lateral aspect, and the projections appearing as similar outline in dorsal, ventral and lateral views (
<figureCitation id="13544590FF9AFFADFD3DC590FCC0C7F5" box="[726,819,655,681]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1860,1884]" captionTargetBox="[284,1303,184,1825]" captionTargetId="figure-30@3.[283,1303,181,1836]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Rhopalopsole magnispina sp. n., male. a. terminalia, dorsal view; b. terminalia, ventral view; c. terminalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6577756" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6577756/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="96">Figs. 2a</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13544590FF9AFFADFCD4C590FC70C7F6" box="[831,899,655,682]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1924,1948]" captionTargetBox="[200,1384,188,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-18@4.[192,1395,181,1900]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Rhopalopsole magnispina sp. n., male. a. terminalia, dorsal view; b. terminalia, ventral view; c. central plate, transverse bars and epiproct, dorsal view; d. epiproct, anterolateral view; e. epiproct, caudal view; f. tergum 10, lateral view. cp=central plate, tb=transverse bars." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6577759" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6577759/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="96">3a, 3f</figureCitation>
). Cercus curved upcurved medially in the usual manner, without apical spine (
<figureCitation id="13544590FF9AFFADFE07C5ACFD81C791" box="[492,626,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1860,1884]" captionTargetBox="[284,1303,184,1825]" captionTargetId="figure-30@3.[283,1303,181,1836]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Rhopalopsole magnispina sp. n., male. a. terminalia, dorsal view; b. terminalia, ventral view; c. terminalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6577756" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6577756/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="96">Figs. 2a, 2c</figureCitation>
). Epiproct flattened, regularly widened to arcuately notched apex (
<figureCitation id="13544590FF9AFFADFA8FC5ACFF47C7AD" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1860,1884]" captionTargetBox="[284,1303,184,1825]" captionTargetId="figure-30@3.[283,1303,181,1836]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Rhopalopsole magnispina sp. n., male. a. terminalia, dorsal view; b. terminalia, ventral view; c. terminalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6577756" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6577756/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="96">Figs. 2a</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13544590FF9AFFADFF54C5C8FEDCC7AD" box="[191,303,727,753]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1924,1948]" captionTargetBox="[200,1384,188,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-18@4.[192,1395,181,1900]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Rhopalopsole magnispina sp. n., male. a. terminalia, dorsal view; b. terminalia, ventral view; c. central plate, transverse bars and epiproct, dorsal view; d. epiproct, anterolateral view; e. epiproct, caudal view; f. tergum 10, lateral view. cp=central plate, tb=transverse bars." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6577759" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6577759/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="96">3a, 3c–3e</figureCitation>
). Subanal lobe of large for genus, distinctly sclerotized, strongly upcurved apically at midlength, dorsal and ventral aspects each with two large curved hooks; the dorsal portion clearly bipartite, with two membranous finger-like apical lobes, in lateral and caudal view, and the mesoventral portion bears a pair of darkly sclerotized nipple-like projection (
<figureCitation id="13544590FF9AFFADFE73C45CFDECC601" box="[408,543,835,861]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1860,1884]" captionTargetBox="[284,1303,184,1825]" captionTargetId="figure-30@3.[283,1303,181,1836]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Rhopalopsole magnispina sp. n., male. a. terminalia, dorsal view; b. terminalia, ventral view; c. terminalia, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6577756" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6577756/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="96">Figs. 2a–2b</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13544590FF9AFFADFDC1C45CFD82C601" box="[554,625,835,861]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1924,1948]" captionTargetBox="[200,1384,188,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-18@4.[192,1395,181,1900]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Rhopalopsole magnispina sp. n., male. a. terminalia, dorsal view; b. terminalia, ventral view; c. central plate, transverse bars and epiproct, dorsal view; d. epiproct, anterolateral view; e. epiproct, caudal view; f. tergum 10, lateral view. cp=central plate, tb=transverse bars." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6577759" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6577759/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="96">3a–3b</figureCitation>
, 
