<subSubSection id="C3750A9EFF9AFFADFF2CC37CFBE1C1B6" pageId="2" pageNumber="96" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD05915FF9AFFADFF2CC37CFBE1C1B6" blockId="2.[151,1437,259,1258]" pageId="2" pageNumber="96">
<emphasis id="B91B8507FF9AFFADFF2CC37CFEC8C121" bold="true" box="[199,315,1123,1149]" pageId="2" pageNumber="96">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C6F2296FF9AFFADFEAEC37CFD98C121" authority="Li &amp; Zhang &amp; Yang &amp; Li, 2022" authorityName="Li &amp; Zhang &amp; Yang &amp; Li" authorityYear="2022" box="[325,619,1123,1149]" class="Insecta" family="Leuctridae" genus="Rhopalopsole" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="96" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="magnispina" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B91B8507FF9AFFADFEAEC37CFD98C121" box="[325,619,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="96">Rhopalopsole magnispina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B91B8507FF9AFFADFD9EC37CFD22C121" bold="true" box="[629,721,1123,1149]" pageId="2" pageNumber="96">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A228387CFF9AFFADFD9EC37CFD22C121" box="[629,721,1123,1149]" pageId="2" pageNumber="96" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is a typical member of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6F2296FF9AFFADFC02C37BFB69C121" authorityName="Yang &amp; Yang" authorityYear="1994" box="[1001,1178,1123,1149]" class="Insecta" family="Leuctridae" genus="Rhopalopsole" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="96" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shaanxiensis">
<emphasis id="B91B8507FF9AFFADFC02C37BFB69C121" box="[1001,1178,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="96">R. shaanxiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group as proposed by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFE24E4FF9AFFADFF7CC398FE96C1FD" author="Sivec, I. &amp; Harper, P. P. &amp; Shimizu, T." box="[151,357,1159,1185]" pageId="2" pageNumber="96" pagination="1 - 122" refId="ref2781" refString="Sivec, I., Harper, P. P. &amp; Shimizu, T. (2008) Contribution to the study of the Oriental genus Rhopalopsole (Plecoptera: Leuctridae). Scopolia, 64, 1 - 122." type="journal article" year="2008">
Sivec 
<emphasis id="B91B8507FF9AFFADFF37C397FEE7C1FD" box="[220,276,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="96">et al.</emphasis>
(2008)
</bibRefCitation>
with strongly ornamental tergum 9 and large and complex subanal lobe. This species can be easily distinguished from other members of the group by the large hook-like spines on subanal lobe, trilobed posteromedial portion of tergum 10, and widened epiproct with arcuately incised apex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
